snippet.title: The Woman in Cabin 10 | Official Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
They don’t want you to believe what she saw.

Based on the bestselling novel The Woman in Cabin 10 by Ruth Ware. While on board a luxury yacht for a travel assignment, a journalist (Keira Knightley) witnesses a passenger thrown overboard late at night, only to be told that it didn’t happen, as all passengers and crew are accounted for. Despite no one believing her, she continues to look for answers, putting her own life in danger.

Watch The Woman in Cabin 10, only on Netflix: https://www.netflix.com/thewomanincabin10

snippet.title: Minecraft 10 Pros vs 1000 Players
snippet.description:
Thank you to SparkedHost for sponsoring this video! Check them out here: https://sparkedhost.com/minecraft-server-hosting/?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=paid_video&utm_campaign=horizon-2025&utm_content=10-pros-vs-1000-players

APPLY TO BE A PRO IN MY NEXT 10v1000 VIDEO: https://apply.antip2w.net/
WANT TO PLAY AMONG THE 1000? JOIN THE EVENT SERVER TO BE PINGED WHEN WE NEED YOU: https://discord.gg/M9AXaqeCbt  
Join 6b6t.org if you want to try out a cool anarchy server where the devs care: mine.6b6t.org
bedrock.6b6t.org for bedrock edition and port 19132
MakersMedia+ video about making my helmet: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HamVXgMR-ZE&t

Hey ya'll! Been a hot minute... But I hope I made the wait just a (little bit) worth it. I have graduated summa cum laude at harvard (no I didn't) and I finally have some free time (im just now attending college guys HELPPPP) but anyways, I got 10 of the best Minecraft players I could find to design and build a fortress for them to try breaking into. I put a $500 cash prize to really up the stakes too. Who would win? Watch to find out!!

TWITTER: https://twitter.com/TheHorizon2b2t
TWITCH (I'm live sometimes): https://www.twitch.tv/thehorizonmc
Biz: horizon@antip2w.net
Anarchy server IP: horizonanarchy.net
Reddit: https://www.reddit.com/r/AntiP2W/

Kenadians POV: not out yet. SCREAM at him to upload!!!
Wato1876s POV: https://youtu.be/QPH6cQy6__g?si=KG4h1Mh_f2vwHdg6
23:50

Animations are done in Blockbuster Mod, very powerful tool. 

[DISCLAIMER] Various events shown in this video may have been re-arranged, exaggerated, or fabricated for entertainment value or ease of story telling. During the actual event, I've tried my best to keep things as fair and reasonable as possible, I'm simply using what I have to the best of my ability to make a fantastic video.

More info:
- You may notice in some parts it says "2/~300" people sleeping, which implies that the server does not in fact have 1000 people. Its misleading; the way our server software, Multipaper, manages 1000 people is by splitting up the world into multiple threads (or basically, multiple different worlds all synchronously stitched into one). I should also mention that we weren't able to get a constant stream of 1,000 players, as many players rage quitted or had to leave early- we can't control things like this.
- This really experimental software had issues, some of the base got rolled back so worldedit was used to correct for it. The Pros worked incredibly hard and the worldedit was simply done to reverse their work. There were also many technical issues that happened, and I apologize to any player in this event who had it get in their way. 
- The actual battle was 30 mins. Nothing happened then, so I extended it, so I can have interesting things happen.
- We actually had a bit more than 10 players, and for good reason; for example, Coldified was caught xraying on the resource world and we had to ban him, and so having a few extra players helped in times like those.

Believe it or not I was actually biasing the event to have the outcome be the opposite of what ended up happening, I just underestimated how good the winning party was :)

[IMPORTANT] Here is a document defining what the general community thinks is P2W, and also explains how you can make YOUR server not P2W, in 30 community translated languages!: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Rd8vkKvpln6uhgO4XIUctWS5VkaxyZRc0h8Bb9GaxLI/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: Fallout Season 2 - Official Teaser Trailer | gamescom 2025
snippet.description:
Watch the Season 2 Teaser Trailer for Fallout, the live-action series based on the Bethesda-developed Fallout game series distributed by Amazon MGM Studios, and Kilter Films produced in association with Bethesda Game Studios and Bethesda Softworks.

Fallout is based on one of the most popular video game franchises of all time and is set 200 years after an apocalyptic event. The story follows the gentle denizens of luxury fallout shelters who are forced to return to the irradiated hellscape their ancestors left behind—and are shocked to discover an incredibly complex, gleefully weird, and highly violent universe waiting for them. The brief teaser trailer depicts Lucy MacLean and Cooper Howard venturing off across the wasteland with New Vegas in the distance, calling back to the famous game location in the franchise.

Fallout Season 2 stars Ella Purnell, Aaron Moten, Walton Goggins, Kyle MacLachlan, Moisés Arias, Frances Turner, and more. The Executive Producers for Fallout Season 2 are Jonathan Nolan and Lisa Joy, alongside Geneva Robertson-Dworet and Graham Wagner also serve as executive producers, creators, and showrunners. Todd Howard, Bethesda Game Studios, executive produces along with James Altman for Bethesda Softworks. 

Fallout Season 2 is premiering in December 17, 2025, with the series also being renewed for Season 3.

#IGN #gamescom2025

The time is Sengoku.

Japan is fractured into many independent nations entangled in ceaseless war. At the center lies Ashina, a land of sacred earth and ancient mystery. Two decades after Sword Saint Isshin Ashina reclaimed the region in a brutal coup, a new threat emerges from within: The Interior Ministry. Desperate to protect his homeland, Isshin’s grandson Genichiro turns to forbidden powers. The only hope lies in a kidnapped boy — the Divine Heir — and his silent protector: a loyal shinobi known only as Sekiro.

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

Putting on a drum show.
 
Completed checklist for today,
Now they have to let you out of your cage,
Feeling stuck between a rock and a home,
Two places you do not want to go, so, so.
 
He’s putting on a drum show,
Even now, even now,
He’ll take the longer way home,
Even now, even now,
He’ll never, ever say so,
He drives fast just to feel it, feel it,
He drives slow if his song’s not over,
Drown it out, drown it out.
 
He’d rather feel something than nothing at all,
So he swerves all around as his head starts to fall,
Turns it up,
Stuck between a rock and a home,
Two places he does not want to go, so, so.
 
I’ve been this way,
I want to change.

snippet.title: Stan Walker - Bulletproof/Soul Deep(Mt Zion)/Could You Be Loved
snippet.description:
Stan Walker - Bulletproof/Soul Deep(Mt Zion)/Could You Be Loved 
Subscribe to my channel:  https://www.youtube.com/@StanWalkerAotearoa.
Thought i’d bring back “Bulletproof” with the team…
It’s always been one of my favourite tracks to perform live…
“Soul Deep” is one of my favourite songs from the movie “Mt Zion”. Being able to play the character “Turei” from Pukekohe was one of the biggest honours ever 🔥🔥🔥

It was during our time in Puke and filming that I fell in absolute awe of the king, Robert Nesta Marley(uncle Bob) 🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾

Big mihi to the director/writer/composer of Mt Zion and all the waiata - Te Arepa Kahi for having me apart of such an incredible kaupapa 🔥🔥🔥

So we bringing it back with the team. This is for all our “Mt Zion” fans ✊🏾✊🏾✊🏾

snippet.title: Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War IV Official Announce Trailer | Gamescom Opening Night 2025
snippet.description:
At last, back to war! Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War IV officially revealed during Gamescom Opening Night Live 2025!

Battle for planet Kronus as Warhammer 40,000's ultimate real time strategy game returns, featuring the largest campaign ever with four distinct factions battling it out in epic, brutal large-scale conflicts. 

Dawn of War IV returns to the legendary RTS series’ roots with satisfying gameplay and a brutal, expanded Sync Kill system. Take command of four Warhammer 40,000 factions, including, for the first time in the Dawn of War series, the Adeptus Mechanicus! Fight through 70+ campaign missions solo or with a friend in a story crafted by legendary Black Library author John French. Immerse yourself in endlessly replayable modes including Last Stand and Skirmish, or take the fight to the world with intense multiplayer combat.

Read more on Warhammer Community: https://www.warhammer-community.com/en-gb/articles/l8pdgqps/warhammer-40000-dawn-of-war-iv/

Wishlist NOW on Steam: https://ow.ly/wPeP50WIbWb

Follow for more Warhammer, more often:

- Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/warhammerofficial/
- Threads: https://www.threads.net/@warhammerofficial
- Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/WarhammerOfficial/

About YRF Spy Universe:

The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. snippet.title: Honest Trailers | Jurassic World: Rebirth
snippet.description:
It’s the Honest Trailer for Jurassic World: Rebirth! This wasn’t so bad was it? Or have our standards just fallen that low? Either way this is the same ol’ dino chow they’ve been feeding us since the 90’s, only this time…there’s uh…more Altoids? The humans got better, the dinosaurs got worse, and we’ll all meet back here in two years to say more or less the same things about the next one.
